params.message:
Change container from ethanol to Wash1 in slot 9.
Move plate from 5 to MAG (Step 3), wait 5 min until solution is clear, resume protocol.
Move the plate from MAG to position 2, then resume protocol.
Move plate from 2 to MAG for 3 min or until the solution is clear, then resume the protocol.
Move the plate from MAG to position 2. AND switch wash1 for wash2 in slot 9.
Move plate from 2 to MAG for 3 min or until the solution is clear, then resume protocol.
Move the plate from MAG to position 2, then resume protocol.
Move plate from 2 to MAG for 5 min or until the solution is clear, then resume protocol.

Incubate for 5 min on MAG to allow the ethanol evaporate. 
Move the plate from MAG to position 2, Here you only have the beads.
Resume the protocol.

FILL NEW TIPS in slot 7.
Move from 2 to the Temp. module. Wait 5 min. Put it back on MAG for 5 min or until the solution is clear.
Place the PCR plate to the thermal module (20C). Then resume the protocol.
